description:
Pianist Michel Camilo talks about his unique relationship with George Wein and the Newport Jazz Festival. Camilo also recalls some of his most memorable moments at the festival.  And he tries to explain what is special about the festival. This interview was done during the 2013 Newport Jazz Festival, where Camilo performed with his sextet. 

Interview by Lee Mergner.  Video by Melissa Mergner.  Sound by Jen Kim.  Thanks to Carolyn McClair, Melanie Nanez, Danny Melnick and the staff of the Newport Jazz Festival for their support.
